<p>Imperial units are commonly used in the United States and a few other countries. Measures
provides seamless conversion between Imperial and SI units.</p>

<h3>Length</h3>

<pre><code class="language-lean">open Measures.Units.Imperial

def height := 6.0 *: foot
def width := 24.0 *: inch
def road := 5.0 *: mile
def fabric := 3.0 *: yard

-- Convert to SI
#eval height.asUnit meter  -- ~1.83 m
#eval road.asUnit kilometer  -- ~8.05 km</code></pre>

<h3>Mass</h3>

<pre><code class="language-lean">def weight := 180.0 *: pound
def package := 32.0 *: ounce

-- Convert to SI
#eval weight.asUnit kilogram  -- ~81.6 kg</code></pre>

<h3>Velocity</h3>

<pre><code class="language-lean">def carSpeed := 60.0 *: milePerHour
def windSpeed := 25.0 *: milePerHour

-- Convert to SI
#eval carSpeed.asUnit meterPerSecond  -- ~26.8 m/s
#eval carSpeed.asUnit kilometer / hour  -- ~96.6 km/h</code></pre>

<h3>Cross-System Operations</h3>

<p>Quantities from different unit systems work together seamlessly:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">open Measures.Units.SI
open Measures.Units.Imperial

-- Mixed calculations
def roomLength := 12.0 *: foot
def roomWidth := 3.5 *: meter

-- Both are Length dimension - can be combined
def totalLength := roomLength + roomWidth.asUnit foot *: foot

-- Format in preferred unit
#eval roomLength.format meter  -- "3.66 m"
#eval roomWidth.format foot    -- "11.48 ft"</code></pre>

